stions.%20The%20earlier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fquiz.toys%2Farchive%2Fposts%2Fcracking-gei-greyhound%2F%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3ESeries%201-7%3C%2Fa%3E%0Achips%20held%20plaintext%20ASCII%2C%20readable%20in%20any%20hex%20editor.%20Series%208%20shipped%20with%20a%20new%20compressed%20format%2C%20T3%2C%20and%20the%20data%20looked%20like%20noise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20the%20switch%20was%20driven%20by%20anti-cloning%2C%20by%20storage%20efficiency%20(T3%20packs%20three%20times%20as%20many%20questions%20into%20twice%20the%20storage)%2C%20or%20both%2C%20isn%E2%80%99t%20documented%20in%20any%20source%20I%E2%80%99ve%20found.%20The%20later%20T4%2FT5%2FT8%20boards%20did%20add%20a%20PAL%20chip%20dongle%20gating%20decode%20on%20a%20hardware%20signature%2C%20which%20suggests%20anti-tampering%20became%20a%20concern%20at%20some%20point.%20Either%20way%20the%20technical%20effect%20was%20the%20same.%20No%20readable%20text%2C%20Shannon%20entropy%20of%207.4%20bits%20per%20byte%2C%20and%20the%20format%20stayed%20uncracked%20for%2040%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20T3%20format%20shipped%20on%20the%20same%20Z80%20hardware%20family%20as%20the%20earlier%0A%E2%80%9CUT%E2%80%9D%20plaintext%20series%2C%20same%20Toms%20River%20cabinet%2C%20same%20five%20EPROM%0Asockets%2C%20same%20subscription%20model.%20The%20only%20thing%20that%20changed%20was%20the%0Aencoding%20inside%20each%20chip%20and%20the%20addition%20of%20a%20PAL-chip%20dongle%20on%0Alater%20boards%20(T4%20%2F%20T5%20%2F%20T8)%20to%20gate%20decoding%20on%20a%20hardware%20signature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20id%3D%22the-data%22%3EThe%20Data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%2050%2C816%20cracked%20records%20browse%20at%0A%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fquiz.toys%2Farchive%2Fbrowse%3Fsource%3Dgei%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3E%2Fbrowse%3Fsource%3Dgei%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Series%208%20through%2018%2C%0Athe%20gt103%20variant%20pack%2C%20plus%20the%20T5%2FT8%20sister%20formats.%20(Series%20A%20and%0AB%20shipped%20on%20the%20earlier%20plaintext%20%E2%80%9CUT%E2%80%9D%20format%20and%20live%20with%20the%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fquiz.toys%2Farchive%2Fposts%2Fcracking-gei-greyhound%2F%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3EGreyhound%20Electronics%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%0A.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EExtractor%3A%20%3Ccode%3Escripts%2Fgei%2Fextract.py%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ET3%20decompressor%3A%20%3Ccode%3Escripts%2Fgei%2Fformat.py%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20id%3D%22how-we-cracked-it%22%3EHow%20We%20Cracked%20It%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22the-t3-rom%22%3EThe%20T3%20ROM%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20T3%20ROM%20still%20announces%20itself.%20The%20first%20two%20bytes%20are%20%3Ccode%3ET3%3C%2Fcode%3E%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20category%20name%20in%20plaintext%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%20%200000%3A%2054%2033%2053%2050%204F%2052%2054%2053%20FF%201E%2002%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20T3SPORTS...%0A%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20%3Ccode%3E0xFF%3C%2Fcode%3E%20delimiter%3A%20a%202-byte%20little-endian%20question%20count%20(here%20%3Ccode%3E0x021E%3C%2Fcode%3E%20%3D%20542%20questions)%2C%20then%20a%20pointer%20table%2C%20542%20entries%20of%202-byte%20addresses%2C%20same%20structure%20as%20Series%201-7.%20The%20pointers%20are%20self-consistent%3A%20the%20first%20data%20pointer%20matches%20the%20end%20of%20the%20pointer%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20question%20data%20is%20opaque%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%20%20046E%3A%20C0%2025%2009%205D%2000%200D%20CE%2057%207E%207A%201E%2038%2081%204E%20A0%2050%0A%20%20047E%3A%2024%2011%204F%2000%2042%2056%20DC%203D%2049%203E%202E%201D%2085%2006%2085%207E%0A%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20ASCII.%20No%20obvious%20repeating%20patterns.%20Records%20average%2056%20bytes%2C%20too%20short%20for%20plaintext%20questions%20with%20three%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22the-attack%22%3EThe%20Attack%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Ch4%20id%3D%22step-1-capture-decoded-output%22%3EStep%201%3A%20Capture%20Decoded%20Output%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Z80%20firmware%20knows%20how%20to%20decode%20these%20questions%2C%20it%20does%20it%20every%20time%20a%20player%20drops%20a%20quarter.%20So%20we%20let%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20MAME%20Lua%20script%20automated%20gameplay%3A%20insert%20coin%2C%20select%20category%2C%20wait%20for%20the%20question%20to%20render%2C%20then%20read%20the%20decoded%20text%20buffer%20at%20address%20%3Ccode%3E%244090%3C%2Fcode%3E.%20The%20game%E2%80%99s%20own%20CPU%20did%20the%20decompression%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22highlight%22%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%20style%3D%22color%3A%23f8f8f2%3Bbackground-color%3A%23272822%3B-moz-tab-size%3A4%3B-o-tab-size%3A4%3Btab-size%3A4%22%3E%3Ccode%20class%3D%22language-lua%22%20data-lang%3D%22lua%22%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22display%3Aflex%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2375715e%22%3E--%20Read%20decoded%20question%20from%20game's%20text%20buffer%3C%2Fspan%3E%0A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22display%3Aflex%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Efor%3C%2Fspan%3E%20i%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23f92672%22%3E%3D%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ae81ff%22%3E0%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ae81ff%22%3E255%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Edo%3C%2Fspan%3E%0A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22display%3Aflex%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Elocal%3C%2Fspan%3E%20b%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23f92672%22%3E%3D%3C%2Fspan%3E%20space%3Aread_u8(%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ae81ff%22%3E0x4090%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23f92672%22%3E%2B%3C%2Fspan%3E%20i)%0A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22display%3Aflex%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Eif%3C%2Fspan%3E%20b%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23f92672%22%3E%3D%3D%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ae81ff%22%3E0x04%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Ethen%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Ebreak%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Eend%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2375715e%22%3E--%20end%20marker%3C%2Fspan%3E%0A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22display%3Aflex%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%20%20%20%20%20...%0A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22display%3Aflex%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%2366d9ef%22%3Eend%3C%2Fspan%3E%0A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E67%20unique%20decoded%20questions%20captured%2C%20each%20with%20full%20text%20and%20three%20answers.%20Now%20we%20had%20known%20plaintext.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch4%20id%3D%22step-2-find-the-rom-pointer%22%3EStep%202%3A%20Find%20the%20ROM%20Pointer%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20the%20decoded%20text%20is%20useless%20without%20knowing%20which%20ROM%20record%20produced%20it.%20We%20needed%20the%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDumping%20RAM%20from%20%3Ccode%3E%244000%3C%2Fcode%3E-%3Ccode%3E%244070%3C%2Fcode%3E%20alongside%20each%20decoded%20question%20revealed%20that%20address%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Ccode%3E%244037%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20held%20a%2016-bit%20pointer%20into%20the%20question%20ROM%2C%20the%20address%20of%20the%20current%20record%E2%80%99s%20data.%20Cross-referencing%20these%20pointers%20against%20the%20ROM%E2%80%99s%20pointer%20table%20confirmed%20the%20match.%20We%20now%20had%2019%20confirmed%20pairs%3A%20exact%20ROM%20bytes%20mapped%20to%20exact%20decoded%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch4%20id%3D%22step-3-the-numbers-dont-add-up%22%3EStep%203%3A%20The%20Numbers%20Don%E2%80%99t%20Add%20Up%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20observation%3A%20the%20math%20was%20wrong%20for%20every%20simple%20encoding%20we%20tried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20confirmed%20pair%2C%20%E2%80%9CHOW%20MANY%20SETS%20ARE%20IN%20A%20FULL-LENGTH%20MEN%E2%80%99S%20CHAMPIONSHIP%20TENNIS%20MATCH%E2%80%9D%20with%20answers%20%E2%80%9CFIVE%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CTHREE%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CSEVEN%E2%80%9D%2C%20decoded%20to%2088%20intermediate%20character%20values.%20The%20ROM%20record%20was%2046%20bytes.%20That%E2%80%99s%204.18%20bits%20per%20character.%20Not%208%20(plaintext)%2C%20not%205%20(5-bit%20packing)%2C%20not%204%20(nibbles).%20Nothing%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorse%2C%20different%20questions%20had%20different%20ratios%2C%202.6%20to%205.7%20bits%20per%20character.%20A%20fixed-width%20encoding%20was%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch4%20id%3D%22step-4-disassemble-the-decompressor%22%3EStep%204%3A%20Disassemble%20the%20Decompressor%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20was%20in%20the%20firmware.%20Cross-referencing%20references%20to%20the%20%3Ccode%3E%244090%3C%2Fcode%3E%20buffer%20and%20the%20%3Ccode%3E%244037%3C%2Fcode%3E%20ROM%20pointer%20led%20to%20Z80%20code%20at%20%3Ccode%3E%242D00%3C%2Fcode%3E-%3Ccode%3E%242D75%3C%2Fcode%3E%2C%20the%20decompression%20loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20code%20reads%20two%20bytes%20from%20ROM%2C%20extracts%20three%205-bit%20values%20through%20a%20sequence%20of%20shifts%20and%20masks%2C%20writes%20them%20to%20the%20buffer%20in%20a%20shuffled%20order%20(positions%200%2C%202%2C%201)%2C%20then%20checks%20the%20high%20bit%20for%20a%20separator%20flag.%20When%20four%20separators%20have%20been%20emitted%2C%20decompression%20is%20complete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22the-algorithm%22%3EThe%20Algorithm%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEach%202-byte%20word%20packs%20three%205-bit%20values%20into%2015%20bits.%20The%2016th%20bit%20is%20a%20field%20separator%20flag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%20%20byte2%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20byte1%0A%20%20%E2%94%8C%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%AC%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%AC%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%90%20%E2%94%8C%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2%94%80%E2